[[Image:rape_equals_love!.jpg|thumb]]A term used in [[fanfiction]] to note an often [[subtext|impossible]] homosexual relationship between two fictional characters, coming from the typical notation of "Character A/Character B." Logically it should encompass all pairings, but the [[logic]] of [[fandom]] is not earth logic, and heterosexual pairings are usually called "het".

Slash is the realm of [[Sick fuck|fucking sickos]] who are too weird for normal society, but not perverted enough to be a [[furry]]. They often write passages like "''... and then Harry reached up to stroke the angelic face of his one true love, Ron Weasley. So much had happened in the last 24 hours: realizing that Ron shared the same feelings, the loss of his virginity, and his expulsion from Hogwart's for embracing that love. It didn't matter what those other witches and wizards might think... he and Ron were meant to be, and that was all that DID matter. Then he gently stuck his...''"

Many slashfic writers are [[16-year-old girl|teenage girls]] who are violently opposed to [[het]]fic, and spend their days [[squee]]ing over their favorite Hawt pairing and writing [[pr0n|smut]]. A subdivision of slashfic is femmeslash - or lesbian fics. By extrapolation, these are probably written by horny [[13 year old boys|teenage boys]]. Most people use slash when referring to either gay or lesbian pairings, but if you want to be accurate, you should denote which it is.

Random Fact:  Many fandoms are over 50% slash.  Out of the 50%, you will find many, many bad sex scenes and a horrifying number of [[mpreg|male pregnancies]]. However, you can always be grateful that it isn't [[fanart]]. Nobody HAS to read bad slash - googling for a random image and being inundated with naked elves is not pleasant. Unless you like that kind of thing, of course.

NOTE: This has everything to do with [[Slashdot]]. Those [[basement dwelling]] [[nerd]]s write it up about the editors all the time. 

